# shorewalld extra arguments
#
# This file is sourced by shorewalld.service and shorewalld@.service via
# EnvironmentFile.  Set SHOREWALLD_ARGS to pass additional flags to
# shorewalld without modifying the unit file.
#
# Examples:
#
#   Enable multi-instance config management with the control socket:
#   SHOREWALLD_ARGS="--instance fw:/etc/shorewall --control-socket /run/shorewalld/control.sock"
#
#   Enable IP-list tracker with a control socket:
#   SHOREWALLD_ARGS="--control-socket /run/shorewalld/control.sock"
#
#   Watch allowlist for changes automatically (conflicts with explicit reload hooks):
#   SHOREWALLD_ARGS="--instance fw:/etc/shorewall --monitor"
#
# See `shorewalld --help` for the full list of options.
#
#SHOREWALLD_ARGS=""
